{
  "texts": [
    "Ganguli et al.",
    "write: \"… certain capabilities (or even entire areas of competency) may be unknown until an input happens to be provided that solicits such knowledge.",
    "Even after a model is trained, creators and users may not be aware of most of its (possibly harmful) capabilities.",
    "These properties become more pronounced as the models scale -larger models tend to be harder to characterize than smaller ones.",
    "… Pre-trained generative models can also be fine-tuned on new data in order to solve new problems."
  ]
}